        public static final boolean isFromV1(byte orig)
        Indicate if the origin is from a Valentine One whether checksum, no checksum or Legacy
        Parameters:
        orig - Origin to check
        Returns:
        True if the origin is from a Valentine One

      • makeFromBufferLE

        public static final ESPPacket makeFromBufferLE(PacketFactory factory,
                                               ByteList buffer,
                                               DeviceId v1Type)
        Creates an ESPPacket with the ESP byte data in buffer.
        Parameters:

        buffer - Buffer holding byte data
        v1Type - V1 type
        Returns:

      • removeDelimitersDLEBytes

        public static final byte[] removeDelimitersDLEBytes(byte[] packetData)
        Removes data link escape bytes as well as removes the Android BT packets. NOTE: This function assumes packetData is a valid, delimited Android BT packet
        Parameters:
        packetData - Android BT packet to strip of Android BT packet formatting
        Returns:
        Byte array contain the raw transmitted ESP data

      • validateFrameChecksum

        public static final boolean validateFrameChecksum(byte[] packetData)
        Validates an array of Android BT packet data to determine if the checksum is valid NOTE: This function assumes that packetData contains a both a start and end packet delimiter bytes and packet Checksum at the second to last position
        Parameters:
        packetData - Android BT packet to validate
        Returns:
        True if the packetData is a valid Android BT packet

      • makeFromBufferSPP

        public static final ESPPacket makeFromBufferSPP(PacketFactory factory,
                                                ByteList buffer,
                                                DeviceId v1Type)
        Utility method for creating an ESP packet from the SPP byte data inside of buffer.
        Parameters:
        factory - Packet Factory
        buffer - Buffer containing ESP byte data
        v1Type - Last known V1 type (this is used as a hint for determining if checksums are used)
        Returns:
        ESPPacket constructed using the ESP byte data in buffer. Null if the data contained in buffer is in valid.

      • calculateChecksumFor

        public static final byte calculateChecksumFor(byte[] data,
                                              int length)
        Utility method for calculating a checksum by summing the bytes in data.
        Parameters:
        data - Source array
        length - number of bytes to use when calculating the checksum.
        Returns:
        Checksum calculate from data. If data is empty, zero is returned.
